		<description><![CDATA[I used to hike in and around Yosemite National Park. To me (and I imagine thousands of other visitors), Yosemite was the embodiment of &#8220;nature,&#8221; something grand, pristine, and, well &#8220;natural.&#8221; Of course there is a sense in which that is true: Yosemite was not made by the hand of man. But in another sense that understanding [...]]]></description>
		<wfw:commentRss>http://newbooksinhistory.com/2012/04/20/jen-huntley-the-making-of-yosemite-james-mason-hutchings-and-the-origins-of-americas-most-popular-national-park-up-of-kansas-2011/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
